#TD                   INTRODUCTORY NOTES

   The on-line tutorials assist you in learning the skills and
   concepts needed to use 20/20.  The advanced techniques tutorials
   introduce some of 20/20's more powerful features.

   If you have never used a spreadsheet before, you will probably
   want to start with the Basic Skills tutorials.  If you are an
   experienced spreadsheet user, you may want to start with the
   Advanced Techniques tutorials.

   Before you begin, there are five things you should know:

    1. The tutorials are selected from a screen menu.  The menu also
       has an option which explains some of the specially defined
       20/20 keys.  You might find it helpful to compare this section
       with your 20/20 keyboard template.

           PRESS <CR> FOR NEXT PAGE.
#TF#TR#/#TT
#TB#TD    2. While using the tutorial you will be asked to type
       certain phrases or press certain keys.  You must type
       the requested characters exactly as indicated, including 
       slashes (/) and parentheses.  The only exceptions are 
       phrases in angle brackets (< >), which indicate special keys,
       such as <CR> for the return key or <UP> for the up arrow key.

    3. If, at any point, you want 20/20 to type the requested input
       for you, press the continue key, called <CONT>.  The <CONT>
       key is defined on the key card for your terminal, in on-line
       HELP, or in the 20/20 Reference Manual.

    4. If you want to stop any tutorial before it ends, press the
       backout key, called <BKO>.  20/20 will ask you if you really
       want to abort the tutorial.  If you answer YES, you will
       leave the tutorial system but will not exit 20/20.  If you 
       answer NO, your current tutorial will continue.

           PRESS <CR> FOR NEXT PAGE.
#TF#TR#/#TT
#TB#TD
    5. To run the tutorial called Advanced Techniques Tutorial:
       Graphics, your terminal or monitor must be a graphics output
       device.  If you are not sure, check your machine manual or ask
       your system manager.



   If you have questions about what you see, the 20/20 manual has a
   full reference section, and a complete glossary and index.
   If you need help with a problem, call the 20/20 Hotline at
   617-655-7824.



 
